# Optional: persist admin CMS on Vercel / serverless (no writable disk).
# Create a free database at https://console.upstash.com → copy REST URL + token.
# In Vercel: Project → Settings → Environment Variables → add both.
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=

# --- Image uploads on Vercel (required for admin uploads in production) ---
# Vercel serverless cannot write to public/. Without Blob, /api/upload returns 503.
#
# 1. Vercel Dashboard → your Project → Storage → Create → Blob (public or private).
# 2. Link the store to this project. Vercel adds BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN for Production
#    (and Preview if you chose it).
# 3. Redeploy (Deployments → … → Redeploy) so the new env is available.
# 4. Local dev: run `vercel link` then `vercel env pull` to get BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN in .env.local
#
# Limit: server uploads through this API are capped at ~4.5MB on Vercel (platform limit).
# Docs: https://vercel.com/docs/storage/vercel-blob/server-upload
BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN=
